result.name: The Grill at Grand Hyatt Hong Kong

html_attributions: The Grill at Grand Hyatt Hong Kong

reviews.text: Excellent service. Extensive wine list and well prepared cocktails, as expected in a five star hotel. Reservations recommended.

I was so terribly disappointed in the service we received at what is supposed to be one of the best hotels in HK. The staff were so reluctant to help (possibly because at least half did not understand English) when I first asked to move to a table with a fan (in 31 degrees). We were not hotel guests so we may have been the only people not using the pool! A fan is the only way to stave off the heat when you're outdoors. Then the waiters kept getting our drink orders wrong and there was a whole frustrating back and forth where not one, not two but four different waiters were called before the issue could be sorted. The food was average and in no way made up for the terrible service. The saving grace was Augusto, the only waiter who seemed to care what we wanted and got the job done. Without him, this review would easily have only one star.

Great setting right by the pool outside! Very good barbecue, seafood and salad buffet. Nice views. Excellent service. Extensive wine list and well prepared cocktails, as expected in a five star hotel. Reservations recommended.
Good place to have your own rest
